#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:1
msgid "Fuzzing and Differential Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:3
msgid ""
"The happy path through cuda-oxide is easy to test with examples: `vecadd`, "
"`gemm`, `sharedmem`, and friends prove that known programs still work. But "
"compilers do not only fail on known programs. They fail on the weird little "
"corners no one thought to write by hand -- the cast after the branch, the "
"tuple inside the call terminator, the integer width that nobody invited to "
"the party."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:9
msgid "That is where fuzzing enters the picture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:11
msgid ""
"cuda-oxide uses a small rustlantis-based harness to generate random custom "
"MIR programs, run them through both the normal Rust CPU backend and cuda-"
"oxide's GPU backend, and compare a compact trace of intermediate values. The "
"aim is not to prove all of Rust correct on GPUs. The aim is more modest, and "
"more useful: stress the MIR importer, lowering pipeline, LLVM export, PTX "
"generation, and runtime execution with programs we did not hand-author."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:20
msgid "What We Are Comparing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:22
msgid ""
"At first glance, \"compare CPU and GPU execution\" sounds suspicious. CPUs "
"and GPUs have different execution models: one scalar thread versus thousands "
"of SIMT lanes, divergent control flow, different memory spaces, different "
"synchronization rules. A general CPU-vs-GPU semantic comparison would be a "
"very fancy way to lie to ourselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:28
msgid "So the harness deliberately avoids that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:30
msgid "It runs generated MIR as a scalar GPU program:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:32
msgid "<<<1, 1>>>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:36
msgid ""
"One block. One thread. No inter-thread communication. No scheduling drama. "
"The GPU is being used as a second codegen target for the same scalar MIR, "
"not as a parallel programming model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:40
msgid "The comparison is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:42
msgid ""
"same generated MIR\n"
"  -> normal rustc/LLVM CPU execution\n"
"  -> cuda-oxide -> LLVM IR -> PTX -> CUDA execution\n"
"  -> compare trace hash\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:49
msgid ""
"If the hashes match, the generated program observed the same sequence of "
"intermediate values on both paths. If they differ, something in the cuda-"
"oxide path deserves attention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:54
msgid ""
"The trace is intentionally compact. Instead of copying every intermediate "
"value back to the host, each `dump_var(...)` call folds values into one "
"`u64` using a byte-wise hash. This makes generated tests cheap to run and "
"easy to compare."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:61
msgid "The Moving Pieces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:63
msgid "The fuzzing setup is split into four parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Piece"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Role"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`crates/fuzzer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Shared trace API and vendored rustlantis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`crates/fuzzer/tools/mir_generator.py`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Seed-to-`generated_case.rs` adapter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`crates/fuzzer/tools/run_seed.py`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Batch runner and artifact recorder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`rustlantis-smoke`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Stable CPU/GPU execution harness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:72
msgid ""
"`crates/fuzzer` is a normal workspace crate, but its library surface is "
"`no_std`. Device code imports `trace_reset`, `trace_finish`, and the generic "
"`dump_var` from there. The actual rustlantis source is vendored under "
"`crates/fuzzer/rustlantis`; it is invoked as an external generator, not used "
"as a Rust library dependency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:78
msgid ""
"The `rustlantis-smoke` example lives under `crates/rustc-codegen-cuda/"
"examples/`. It owns the host/GPU launch logic and a small hand-written "
"sanity test, then includes one generated file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:82
msgid ""
"crates/rustc-codegen-cuda/examples/rustlantis-smoke/src/generated_case.rs\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:86
msgid ""
"The fuzzer tools rewrite that file for each seed. Everything else in the "
"example stays stable. This keeps the harness easy to review: if a seed "
"fails, the generated MIR is isolated in one place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:92
msgid "The Seed Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:94
msgid "One seed follows this path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:96
msgid ""
"**Generate.** rustlantis receives a numeric seed and a small config. Same "
"seed plus same config means the same custom-MIR program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:98
msgid ""
"**Extract.** `mir_generator.py` pulls out the first generated "
"`#[custom_mir]` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:100
msgid ""
"**Adapt.** rustlantis emits calls like `dump_var(a, b, c)`. The adapter "
"rewrites those into tuple locals and one generic `fuzzer::dump_var(...)` "
"call, because custom MIR call operands are picky about tuple expressions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:103
msgid ""
"**Inject.** The adapted function and a small wrapper are written to `src/"
"generated_case.rs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:105
msgid ""
"**Run.** `cargo oxide run rustlantis-smoke` executes the CPU oracle and GPU "
"kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:107
msgid ""
"**Classify.** `run_seed.py` records whether the seed passed, mismatched, "
"failed to compile, or exceeded the adapter's current support surface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:110
msgid ""
"The checked-in generated case currently uses seed `19`, because it shows the "
"important property we want from the harness: multiple intermediate dumps, "
"not just one final value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:114
msgid ""
"__rl_dump0 = (Move(_1), Move(_2), Move(_3), Move(_4));\n"
"Call(_9 = dump_var(Move(__rl_dump0)), ReturnTo(bb4), UnwindUnreachable())\n"
"\n"
"__rl_dump1 = (Move(_6),);\n"
"Call(_9 = dump_var(Move(__rl_dump1)), ReturnTo(bb5), UnwindUnreachable())\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:122
msgid ""
"That means the final trace hash includes several values from one point in "
"the program and another value from a later point. It is still compact, but "
"it is no longer merely \"did the return value match?\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:128
msgid "Running It"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:130
msgid "Run one seed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:132
msgid "python3 crates/fuzzer/tools/run_seed.py --seed 192\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:136
msgid "Run a batch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:138
msgid ""
"python3 crates/fuzzer/tools/run_seed.py --start 0 --count 20 --keep-going\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:142
msgid "Useful flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:144
msgid "`--keep-going`: continue after a failing seed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:145
msgid "`--keep-logs`: write logs for passing seeds too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:146
msgid "`--no-build`: reuse an already-built rustlantis generator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:147
msgid ""
"`--append-summary`: append to the existing summary instead of replacing it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:149
msgid ""
"By default, `summary.jsonl` is replaced at the start of each run. This makes "
"it answer the obvious question: \"what happened in the run I just did?\" If "
"you want history, opt in with `--append-summary`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:155
msgid "Reading Results"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:157
msgid "The runner prints one line per seed and then a full summary:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:159
msgid ""
"results:\n"
"  seed 0: UNSUPPORTED [adapter] unsupported dumped type for Stage 2 adapter: "
"u128 (...)\n"
"  seed 1: COMPILE_FAIL [backend] Unsupported construct: Type translation not "
"yet implemented for: RigidTy(Char) (...)\n"
"summary: COMPILE_FAIL=1, UNSUPPORTED=1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:166
msgid "The statuses mean:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "Meaning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`PASS`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "CPU and GPU traces matched"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`MISMATCH`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "CPU and GPU traces differed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`COMPILE_FAIL [backend]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "The adapter produced a case, but cuda-oxide failed it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "`UNSUPPORTED [adapter]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:53
msgid "rustlantis generated MIR, but the adapter declined it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:175
msgid ""
"`MISMATCH` is the result to take most seriously. Both paths compiled and "
"ran, but observed different values. That is a potential backend correctness "
"bug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:178
msgid ""
"`COMPILE_FAIL [backend]` means the generated case made it past the adapter "
"and into cuda-oxide. The failure may still be expected -- for example, a "
"currently unsupported MIR type -- but the backend is the component that "
"rejected it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:182
msgid ""
"`UNSUPPORTED [adapter]` means rustlantis produced a program, but our adapter "
"refused to turn it into a smoke case. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:185
msgid "unsupported dumped type for Stage 2 adapter: u128\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:189
msgid ""
"That usually means the generated MIR had a `dump_var(...)` containing a type "
"our trace API does not yet know how to hash. Today the trace supports:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:192
msgid "bool, i8, i16, i32, i64, u8, u16, u32, u64\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:196
msgid ""
"It does not yet support `u128`, `i128`, `usize`, `isize`, or `char`. Many "
"adapter-level unsupported cases are therefore not \"bad MIR\" and not cuda-"
"oxide bugs. They are simply places where the fuzzer harness has not grown up "
"yet. Compilers, like people, need snacks before they can handle `u128`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:203
msgid "Artifacts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:205
msgid "Per-seed logs live under:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:207
msgid "crates/fuzzer/artifacts/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:211
msgid "Failure logs include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:213
msgid "the seed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:214
msgid "status and stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:215
msgid "reason"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:216
msgid "return code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:217
msgid "command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:218
msgid "full command output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:219
msgid "the generated `generated_case.rs` snapshot, when one exists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:221
msgid ""
"The generated snapshot matters. If a backend failure appears in CI or a long "
"batch run, the log is enough to see the exact MIR-shaped program that "
"triggered it. The seed lets you regenerate it, but the snapshot saves you a "
"round trip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:227
msgid "Current Limits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:229
msgid ""
"The current config is intentionally small. It keeps the first stage focused "
"on scalar custom MIR and backend plumbing rather than every Rust construct "
"at once. That is why many early seeds classify as `UNSUPPORTED [adapter]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:233
msgid "The widening plan is incremental:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:235
msgid ""
"Add trace support for more scalar types (`u128`, `i128`, `usize`, `isize`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:236
msgid ""
"Decide whether and how to support `char` in cuda-oxide's type translation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:237
msgid "Expand control-flow and cast coverage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:238
msgid "Add arrays, tuples, and eventually structs/enums."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:239
msgid "Add minimization for failing seeds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/fuzzing-and-differential-testing.md:241
msgid ""
"That order is deliberate. A fuzzer that generates everything on day one "
"mostly generates noise. A fuzzer that grows one axis at a time tells you "
"what broke, and why. Much friendlier."
msgstr ""
